\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi720\sl360\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Islands Manager is a graphical desktop tool for downloading and managing the Islands software and the cryptographic keys that establish a user\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s identity in Islands. For the Islands launch in 2019, Islands Manager is fully supported for Windows and Mac OSX and supported with some caveats on Linux.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 On Windows and Mac, Islands Manager will download and install }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.virtualbox.org/"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0 VirtualBox}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  to host the Island server. On Linux, Islands Manager will run the Island natively within a Python virtual environment.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Islands Manager contains a built-in, bare-bones }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BitTorrent"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0 BitTorrent}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  client to download the Island software. It will share the Islands download files with other peers as long as you permit it, which we encourage.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Islands Manager is used to start, stop and monitor the local Island server.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Users interested in hosting an Island on a Linux server without a GUI manager should consult }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "scrivlnk://452C1271-142C-4ADB-B754-C3F6C424EE49"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Advanced Topics: Hosting an Island on a Remote Server}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}}